 present day, this language has proven to be a valuable tool for developers around the world.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It enables developers to easily create, process, and manage content on a server, making it an ideal tool for developing dynamic websites that can respond quickly to user requests.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><b><i>Due to its extensive documentation and regular updates, it remains a highly popular choice for developers looking to build efficient and effective web applications. Its flexibility and versatility have made it a go-to language for many developers worldwide.<\/i><\/b><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"PHP_Software_Development-_Evolution_Journey\"><\/span>PHP Software Development- Evolution Journey<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was first created in 1994 by Rasmus Lerdorf as a simple set of Common Gateway Interface (CGI) scripts to help him maintain his personal website.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since then, it has evolved into a powerful tool used by many tech giants like Facebook to build web applications.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is also a popular choice for building content management systems (CMS) like WordPress, Drupal, Shopify, and WooCommerce.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, there are many other aspects that set PHP apart from other programming languages, such as:<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Scripting_Language\"><\/span><b>Scripting Language<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PHP is a versatile scripting language that is widely used for creating dynamic web pages and other web-based applications. It is a server-side language, which means that it is interpreted by the web server and then sent to the client as HTML code.&nbsp; <\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" i